# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the LemonDrop Next.js application following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File**: `package.json`
- **Change**: Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0` as a dependency
- **Package Manager**: npm (used npm install as per project's existing package-lock.json)

### 2. Component Integration
- **File**: `app/layout.js`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component in the body section alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component
  
### 3. Lock File Update
- **File**: `package-lock.json`
- **Change**: Updated to reflect the new dependency and its sub-dependencies

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
- Identified project as Next.js v16.2.1 (App Router)
- Used the Next.js-specific integration path: `@vercel/speed-insights/next`

### Component Placement
Following the official Vercel documentation for Next.js, the `<SpeedInsights />` component was added to the root layout file (`app/layout.js`) within the `<body>` tag. This ensures the Speed Insights tracking is available across all pages of the application.

The component was placed alongside the existing `@vercel/analytics` component, maintaining consistency with the project's existing Vercel integrations.

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build Test**: Ran `npm run build` - Completed successfully with no errors
✅ **Production Build**: Next.js production build generated successfully
✅ **TypeScript Check**: Passed (77ms)
✅ **Static Generation**: All pages generated successfully (4/4 routes)
✅ **Linter**: Pre-existing linting warnings in `app/page.js` unrelated to our changes

## Next Steps

To complete the Speed Insights setup:

1. **Enable in Vercel Dashboard**: Navigate to your Vercel project dashboard and enable Speed Insights from the sidebar
2. **Deploy**: Deploy this update to Vercel (either via `vercel deploy` or through Git integration)
3. **Monitor**: After deployment and user traffic, Speed Insights data will be available in your Vercel project dashboard

## Notes

- The installation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide (fetched on 2026-04-04)
- Speed Insights will automatically track Core Web Vitals metrics
- The component is lightweight and won't impact page performance
- Data collection begins immediately after deployment to Vercel
- Compatible with Next.js 13.5+ (project is using 16.2.1)
